BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:4EeJNgg76sBT0EevloFQV
SUMMARY:IMPROV 100 THURSDAYS- Intro to Improv: Say Yes!\\\, SPRING'26
DTSTAMP:20260326T010723Z
DTSTART:20260326T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Discover Unexpected Productions’ philosophy of improvisation\\\
	, developed over our 43 years of improvising in Seattle! \\nYou’ll learn h
	ow to actively listen\\\, to use your own life to create collaborative sto
	ries\\\, and you’ll work on the fundamental principles of improvisation: w
	hat it means to say\\\, “Yes\\\, And”\\\, how to tell stories that include
	 everyone in the room\\\, how to stop worrying about failing\\\, and the g
	ames and concepts behind what we do on stages around the world! \\nUnder t
	he guidance of one of our best Seattle improv teachers\\\, you will learn 
	to:· \\n\\nBe a Better Listener\\nConquer Fears\\nSpark Creativity\\nMeet 
	New People & Make New Friends\\nBecome a Better Problem Solver\\nGain Conf
	idence·\\nFail With Grace (and Maybe Even Enjoy It)\\nSay Yes More in Your
	 Life\\nGet Out of Your Comfort Zone\\nBecome a Better Public Speaker\\nDi
	scover More About Yourself\\n…and have a blast doing it!\\n\\nTime and Dat
	es: Thursdays for eight (8) weeks\\\, from March 26 to May 24\\\, 7pm to 9
	:30pm \\nNOTE: Attendance at the first session of your course is mandatory
	 as it sets the agenda for the entire quarter. If you think you will have 
	to miss the first class\\\, please consider registering for the next quart
	er. \\nNo Prerequisites. All students begin at this level\\\, even those w
	ith existing improv experience. It’s a prerequisite to the other levels. \
	\nLocation: 5700 6th Ave St\\\, Suite 109\\\, Umbrella Room\\\, Seattle\\\
	, WA 98108 (In Georgetown\\\, south of downtown\\\, with plenty of parking
	.) \\nMaximum Students: 16 \\nCost: Ticket price $295.00 \\nAge: 18 and ab
	ove \\n**Cancellation policy: If you must cancel before the first class\\\
	, we can only offer credit towards the same level class next quarter. We a
	re unable to offer refunds. If you cancel after the first class we cannot 
	offer credit towards a future class. Again\\\, we are unable to offer refu
	nds.\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/improv-100-thursdays-i
	ntro-to-improv-say-yes-spring26/\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/improv-100-thursdays-intro-
	to-improv-say-yes-spring26/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions Improv School ISSAQUAH/EASTSIDE\\\, 1315 NW
	 Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98108\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:09G50XpiQ5o3Q9C7hwSeH
SUMMARY:Loose Cannons 2026
DTSTAMP:20260326T010723Z
DTSTART:20260326T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Loose Cannons is Seattle improv at its most unpredictable. Ever
	y performance at Unexpected Productions in Pike Place Market is a one-of-a
	-kind experience: exciting\\\, unexpected\\\, a little dangerous\\\, and a
	lways ridiculously fun. This is the show where anything can happen and usu
	ally does. \\nPart One: Part One: The night kicks off with a unique perfor
	mance\\\, setting the performers in a new format with special guest improv
	isers showcasing their signature style or a never-before-seen format. Your
	 suggestions fuel the fire\\\, and the improvisers will ignite the stage\\
	\, bringing your ideas to life. \\nPart Two: The second half launches from
	 a single audience suggestion\\\, setting the performers in motion. It mig
	ht start with a song\\\, a monologue\\\, or a rapid-fire group connection 
	game. Whatever emerges will inspire spontaneous stories\\\, surprising twi
	sts\\\, and big comedic swings. \\nLoose Cannons is fueled by audience ide
	as\\\, fearless performers\\\, and the thrill of not knowing what happens 
	next. You light the fuse. They run with it. What they create is entirely u
	p to you.\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/loose-cannons-202
	6/2026-03-26/\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/loose-cannons-2026/2026-03-
	26/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\\\, 1428 Post Alley at the Gum Wall in Pike
	 Place Market\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98101\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
